# Migrate Claude auto-memory to a pointer index

## Step

Resolved when: (1) every non-duplicated fact in the 18 topic pages under
`~/.claude/projects/-Users-joel/memory/` lives as a Brain `.svx` note
(operator facts → `~/.brain/resources/`, converted to `.svx` per the
Brain law; facts already covered by Brain pages or fleet CLAUDE.md are
dropped as duplicates, with a per-page disposition list in this file);
(2) the topic pages are deleted; (3) `MEMORY.md` is rewritten as a
binding rule at the top (no new topic pages; durable facts go to Brain
`.svx`; only pointers live here) followed by one-line pointers to the
relevant Brain pages; (4) `~/.brain` changes are ready for dark-wizard
commit (steering commits). Evidence base:
[periphery survey](../memory-system-review/periphery-survey.svx)
"Claude auto-memory" and the
[decision](../memory-system-repair/decide-claude-auto-memory.svx).
